http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Malgudi-Exp.-engine-gets-decoupled-from-rake/article13976974.ece

The engine of the Mysuru-Yeshwanthpur Malgudi Express got decoupled from the coaches while departing from the city on Saturday.The train pulled out of platform number 4 at 8.15 a.m. when the engine got decoupled and left behind the rake after moving for a few metres. The locomotive pilot who noticed the hitch stopped the engine immediately.The rake was again hitched to the locomotive after which it left the station about 20 minutes behind schedule.